0.text:
Innate: Warwick deals 12 − 46 (based on level) (+ 15% bonus AD) (+ 10% AP) bonus magic damage  on-hit.
While below 50% maximum health, Warwick also  heals for 100% of the post-mitigation damage dealt by Eternal Hunger, increased to 250% while below 25% maximum health.

Active: Warwick  lunges at the target enemy and bites them, dealing 120% AD (+ 100% AP) magic damage plus bonus magic damage based on the target's maximum health,  healing himself for a percentage of the post-mitigation damage dealt, as well as applying  on-hit and on-attack effects, and  life steal at 100% effectiveness.

1.text: While Jaws of the Beast is in effect, Warwick is  displacement immune and clamps his jaw on the target, following all of their movement. Additionally, the abiltiy can be held for extended effects.

2.text: Hold: When Jaws of the Beast is held, Warwick performs the bite as usual, then begins to  charge for 0.5 seconds, during which he  leaps behind the target. The duration is extended if the target is under the effect of a  dash or a  displacement.

0.text: Passive: Warwick gains  bonus attack speed upon basic attacking an enemy who is below  50% of their maximum health, but loses it when not attacking them or switching to a target above the threshold.

1.text: Passive: Warwick senses all enemy  champions on the map who are damaged below  50% of their maximum health by an allied source, marking them with Blood Hunt until they regenerate above the threshold again. He sees trails leading toward them and gains  bonus movement speed while following the path. This bonus is lost for 0.5 seconds upon entering combat with an enemy champion, but will build up again over the next 3.5 seconds.

2.text: Both passive bonuses are increased to 250% against enemies who are below  20% of their maximum health.

3.text: Active: Warwick senses the nearest enemy champion in the area, marking them with Blood Hunt for 8 seconds, gaining the passive bonuses against them regardless of their  current health.

4.text: The active cannot be cast for 3 seconds after entering combat with an enemy champion. Furthermore, while no enemy champions are marked, the cooldown of Blood Hunt drains twice as quickly by being reduced by an additional 1 second each second.

0.text: Active: Warwick gains  damage reduction for up to 2.5 seconds. Primal Howl can be recast after 1 second, and does so automatically after the duration.

1.text: Recast: Warwick howls, ending Primal Howl's effects and  fearing nearby enemies for 1 second,  slowing them by 90%.

2.text: Starting  Infinite Duress' channel while Primal Howl is active will initiate the recast without ending the damage reduction buff prematurely.

0.text: Active: Warwick  leaps in the target direction with  crowd control immunity, stopping upon hitting an enemy champion. He then  knocks them down and  channels for up to 1.5 seconds to  suppress,  reveal, and deal magic damage every 0.25 seconds,  revealing himself in the process.

1.text: Warwick  heals for 100% of all post-mitigation damage he deals to the target during Infinite Duress.

2.text: Infinite Duress applies  on-hit and on-attack effects 3 times, and  life steal at 100% effectiveness.

3.text: Primal Howl can be cast during the dash.
